## 8. mdRQA — All Four Variables Together

Multidimensional RQA was applied to all four variables simultaneously — PM2.5, 
temperature, pressure, and wind — treating each day as a 4-dimensional state 
vector. No time-delay embedding was applied since each variable already represents 
one dimension of the full system.

![mdRQA Plot](fig_mdrqa_plot.png)

*Figure 10. mdRQA recurrence plot of all four variables combined. The periodic 
grid structure reflects the annual recurrence of the full atmospheric system.*

The mdRQA plot shows a striking periodic grid pattern, with recurrence clusters 
at regular ~365-day intervals. The seasonal cycle of the complete atmospheric 
system is far more visible in mdRQA than in any single-variable analysis.

